HEADWORD: Alicyclic
<hw>Al`i*cyc"lic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Org.
Chem.)</fld> <def>pertaining to compounds that have a ring in the
structure, but are not aromatic, as cyclohexane or cyclohexene. Compare
<contr>aliphatic</contr> and <contr>aromatic</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
